{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_69","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/bash -lc \"nl -ba docs/operator_qa.md | sed -n '1,260p'\"","aggregated_output":"     1\t# Offline Operator QA Workflow\n     2\t\n     3\tMilestone 6 is not finished when bundles merely serialize. Before Milestone 10\n     4\tstarts, the team needs one offline workflow that can:\n     5\t\n     6\t- initialize a localized pulse on the fine surface\n     7\t- check that a lightweight smoke evolution behaves stably enough for pre-engine work\n     8\t- compare fine and coarse behavior quantitatively\n     9\t- show the result on the mesh and patch decomposition without opening raw arrays\n    10\t\n    11\t`scripts/06_operator_qa.py` is that workflow.\n    12\t\n    13\t## Inputs\n    14\t\n    15\tThe report reads only local bundle artifacts that were already built by\n    16\t`scripts/03_build_wave_assets.py`:\n    17\t\n    18\t- `config.paths.processed_graph_dir/<root_id>_fine_operator.npz`\n    19\t- `config.paths.processed_graph_dir/<root_id>_coarse_operator.npz`\n    20\t- `config.paths.processed_graph_dir/<root_id>_transfer_operators.npz`\n    21\t- `config.paths.processed_graph_dir/<root_id>_patch_graph.npz`\n    22\t- `config.paths.processed_graph_dir/<root_id>_operator_metadata.json`\n    23\t- optional descriptor / geometry-QA sidecars for extra context\n    24\t\n    25\tNo FlyWire token or network access is required.\n    26\t\n    27\t## Run It\n    28\t\n    29\tInspect one or more explicit root IDs:\n    30\t\n    31\t```bash\n    32\tpython scripts/06_operator_qa.py --config config/local.yaml --root-id 101 --root-id 102\n    33\t```\n    34\t\n    35\tInspect the active selected subset:\n    36\t\n    37\t```bash\n    38\tpython scripts/06_operator_qa.py --config config/local.yaml --limit 4\n    39\t```\n    40\t\n    41\tEquivalent Make target:\n    42\t\n    43\t```bash\n    44\tmake operator-qa CONFIG=config/local.yaml\n    45\t```\n    46\t\n    47\tOptional smoke depth override:\n    48\t\n    49\t```bash\n    50\tpython scripts/06_operator_qa.py --config config/local.yaml --root-id 101 --pulse-steps 12\n    51\t```\n    52\t\n    53\t## Output Layout\n    54\t\n    55\tThe output directory is deterministic for the exact sorted root-id set:\n    56\t\n    57\t```text\n    58\tconfig.paths.operator_qa_dir/root-ids-<sorted-root-ids>/\n    59\t```\n    60\t\n    61\tExample:\n    62\t\n    63\t```text\n    64\tdata/processed/operator_qa/root-ids-101/index.html\n    65\tdata/processed/operator_qa/root-ids-101/report.md\n    66\tdata/processed/operator_qa/root-ids-101/summary.json\n    67\tdata/processed/operator_qa/root-ids-101/101_details.json\n    68\tdata/processed/operator_qa/root-ids-101/101_pulse_initial.svg\n    69\tdata/processed/operator_qa/root-ids-101/101_boundary_mask.svg\n    70\tdata/processed/operator_qa/root-ids-101/101_patch_decomposition.svg\n    71\tdata/processed/operator_qa/root-ids-101/101_fine_pulse_final.svg\n    72\tdata/processed/operator_qa/root-ids-101/101_coarse_pulse_final.svg\n    73\tdata/processed/operator_qa/root-ids-101/101_coarse_reconstruction.svg\n    74\tdata/processed/operator_qa/root-ids-101/101_reconstruction_error.svg\n    75\t```\n    76\t\n    77\tThat path stability is deliberate so the report can be referenced from run logs,\n    78\tticket notes, or review comments.\n    79\t\n    80\t## What It Checks\n    81\t\n    82\tThe current report combines bundle-level structural checks with one\n    83\tstability-oriented pulse smoke loop.\n    84\t\n    85\tStructural checks:\n    86\t\n    87\t- fine and coarse operator symmetry residuals\n    88\t- fine and coarse constant-field nullspace residuals on the stiffness matrices\n    89\t- non-positive mass counts on fine and coarse mass diagonals\n    90\t- coarse-versus-fine Galerkin and application residuals already serialized in\n    91\t  the transfer bundle\n    92\t\n    93\tPulse smoke checks:\n    94\t\n    95\t- deterministic localized pulse initialization from the fine bundle’s stored\n    96\t  geodesic neighborhood data\n    97\t- explicit diffusion-style stepping with `dt` derived from the estimated\n    98\t  largest eigenvalue of the symmetric mass-normalized operator\n    99\t- mass drift across the smoke evolution\n   100\t- Dirichlet-energy monotonicity under the chosen time step\n   101\t- final coarse-vs-restricted-fine residual\n   102\t- final fine-vs-prolongated-coarse residual\n   103\t\n   104\tThe report also renders:\n   105\t\n   106\t- pulse initialization on the fine surface\n   107\t- boundary-mask inspection\n   108\t- patch decomposition\n   109\t- fine pulse after the smoke loop\n   110\t- coarse pulse after the smoke loop\n   111\t- prolongated coarse reconstruction on the fine surface\n   112\t- absolute reconstruction error on the fine surface\n   113\t\n   114\t## Gate Semantics\n   115\t\n   116\tEvery metric gets `pass`, `warn`, or `fail`. The aggregate report also emits a\n   117\tMilestone 10 gate:\n   118\t\n   119\t- `go`: no warnings or failures\n   120\t- `review`: no blocking failures, but at least one warning or non-blocking failure\n   121\t- `hold`: at least one blocking failure\n   122\t\n   123\tUse that gate this way:\n   124\t\n   125\t- `go`: acceptable baseline for downstream engine integration and solver work\n   126\t- `review`: engine work can continue only if a reviewer signs off on the\n   127\t  degraded metrics and the visual overlays still look scientifically plausible\n   128\t- `hold`: do not treat the operator bundle as an engine baseline; rebuild or\n   129\t  debug the bundle first\n   130\t\n   131\t## Reviewer Checklist\n   132\t\n   133\tReviewers should look for:\n   134\t\n   135\t- pulse initialization staying localized around one seed region rather than\n   136\t  starting already smeared across the whole surface\n   137\t- boundary masks matching the intended surface topology instead of lighting up\n   138\t  unexpected interior structure\n   139\t- fine smoke evolution diffusing smoothly without explosive growth or obvious\n   140\t  checkerboard artifacts\n   141\t- coarse pulse support following the same broad region as the restricted fine\n   142\t  result\n   143\t- prolongated coarse reconstruction tracking the fine field instead of\n   144\t  collapsing onto a few dominant patches\n   145\t- reconstruction error concentrating near coarse partition limits rather than\n   146\t  covering the whole neuron\n   147\t\n   148\tWhen the report fails:\n   149\t\n   150\t- if symmetry, nullspace, or non-positive-mass checks fail, stop Milestone 10\n   151\t  work and inspect the operator build itself\n   152\t- if pulse mass or energy checks fail, treat the bundle as numerically unstable\n   153\t  for pre-engine use\n   154\t- if only coarse-vs-fine comparison checks warn or fail, inspect the patch\n   155\t  decomposition and transfer quality before deciding whether the bundle is still\n   156\t  usable for exploratory work\n   157\t\n   158\t## Threshold Overrides\n   159\t\n   160\tOptional overrides live under `meshing.operator_qa_thresholds` in the config and\n   161\tfollow the same shape as the geometry-QA thresholds:\n   162\t\n   163\t```yaml\n   164\tmeshing:\n   165\t  operator_qa_thresholds:\n   166\t    pulse_final_fine_vs_prolongated_coarse_residual_relative:\n   167\t      warn: 0.25\n   168\t      fail: 0.60\n   169\t      blocking: false\n   170\t```\n   171\t\n   172\tTighten thresholds when using the workflow as a release gate. Relax them only\n   173\twhen the report is being used for exploratory analysis and the deviation is\n   174\tdocumented explicitly.\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_70","type":"agent_message","text":"Implemented FW-M6-005 with a new offline operator QA workflow in [operator_qa.py](/home/jack/Documents/github/personal/fly_neural_simulation/flywire_wave_repo/src/flywire_wave/operator_qa.py) and the CLI entrypoint [06_operator_qa.py](/home/jack/Documents/github/personal/fly_neural_simulation/flywire_wave_repo/scripts/06_operator_qa.py). It reads existing local Milestone 6 bundles, builds a deterministic geodesic-localized pulse, runs a lightweight stability smoke evolution on fine and coarse operators, scores symmetry/nullspace/mass/transfer/pulse metrics with pass/warn/fail semantics plus a `milestone10_gate`, and writes a deterministic static report bundle: `index.html`, `report.md`, `summary.json`, per-root detail JSON, and SVG overlays for pulse init, boundary masks, patch decomposition, coarse reconstruction, and reconstruction error. I also wired a default `operator_qa_dir` config path and `make operator-qa`.\n\nAdded fixture coverage in [test_operator_qa.py](/home/jack/Documents/github/personal/fly_neural_simulation/flywire_wave_repo/tests/test_operator_qa.py) so the script is exercised end to end and asserts deterministic output paths plus summary fields. Documented the workflow, gate semantics, and reviewer checklist in [operator_qa.md](/home/jack/Documents/github/personal/fly_neural_simulation/flywire_wave_repo/docs/operator_qa.md), with a short contract note in [pipeline_notes.md](/home/jack/Documents/github/personal/fly_neural_simulation/flywire_wave_repo/docs/pipeline_notes.md). Pre-existing unrelated worktree changes were left untouched.\n\nVerified with `./.venv/bin/python -m unittest tests.test_operator_qa -v` and `make test` (`40` tests, all passing)."}}
